Description:
    Adds a module to the app

Example:
    yo cfsg:module

    Modules are a pattern to group related views, models, and collections.

    For example the Friends module would contain all JavaScript, Handlebars,
    and Stylus code related to Friends data in the app.

    Modules have a sensible directory structure:

        /source/js/modules/<ModuleName>.js
            JavaScript code for the module's models, views, and collections

        /source/templates/<module-name>/<view-name>.html
            Handlebars HTML templates for a module's views

        /source/styles/modules/<module-name>/<view-name>.styl
            Stylus CSS definitions for a module's views

    Tip: Use the cfsg:mvc generator to add models, collections, or views to
    existing modules.
